net.cloud.server.event.command.parameter

Class CommandParameter<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.cloud.server.event.command.parameter.CommandParameter<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - The type of the value held by the parameter
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OptionalParameter, RequiredParameter

    public abstract class CommandParameter<V>
extends Object
    A parameter is what a Command expects to be provided as a variable of sorts. A parameter contains an argument, which holds the actual value.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CommandParameter

        public CommandParameter(CommandArgument<V> argument)
        Creates a new Parameter, with the specified argument. This is intended to be a prototype argument, and parameters can later then be added to a command via newParsedInstance(String)
        For example: new RequiredParameter(ArgumentPrototyeps.STRING)
        Parameters:
        argument - The argument - a Prototype - to specify what type the argument should be

    • Method Detail

      • newParsedInstance

        public abstract CommandParameter<V> newParsedInstance(String valueString)
                                               throws CommandException
        Create a new instance of the parameter. This is useful for creating an instance of the same type, without necessarily knowing the type (letting dynamic binding do the work) The new instance is not a clone, and the details are left to the subclass. The valueString is used to create a new argument within the parameter
        Parameters:
        valueString - The string that will be parsed into the new value
        Returns:
        A new CommandParameter instance, of the same type, with the given new value
        Throws:
        CommandException - If parsing is not successful
